{"questionId":"9069731","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chloroquine is a medication used to prevent and treat malaria.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/2deecddd42a02b9b48eb3051754d77d8960aaaac.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chloroquine can be synthesized by reacting 4,7-dichloroquinoline with another reactant, <strong>B</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/30d1c38e0e599948a6a57bb8782260e72e980dde.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 4,7-dichloroquinoline&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; chloroquine</strong></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>This reaction can be done with a copper catalyst. State the ground-state electron&nbsp;configuration for copper.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>1s<sup>2</sup>2s<sup>2</sup>2p<sup>6</sup>3s<sup>2</sup>3p<sup>6</sup>4s<sup>1</sup>3d<sup>10</sup> / 1s<sup>2</sup>2s<sup>2</sup>2p<sup>6</sup>3s<sup>2</sup>3p<sup>6</sup>3d<sup>10</sup>4s<sup>1</sup></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>[Ar]4s<sup>1</sup>3d<sup>10</sup> / [Ar]3d<sup>10</sup>4s<sup>1</sup> ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069731","referenceCode":"22N.2.hl.TZ0.e.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"This reaction can be done with a copper catalyst. State the ground-state electron configuration for copper.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure","2.2 Electron configuration","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}